<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Dwivedi Vijay Prakash | NTU NAIL</title><link>https://ntu-nail.github.io/author/dwivedi-vijay-prakash/</link><atom:link href="https://ntu-nail.github.io/author/dwivedi-vijay-prakash/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>Dwivedi Vijay Prakash</description><generator>Hugo Blox Builder (https://hugoblox.com)</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 01 Jun 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://ntu-nail.github.io/author/dwivedi-vijay-prakash/avatar_hu0647a3e11cc51fc0d74b2dc45ca2f8e2_314716_270x270_fill_q75_lanczos_center.jpg</url><title>Dwivedi Vijay Prakash</title><link>https://ntu-nail.github.io/author/dwivedi-vijay-prakash/</link></image><item><title>Dwivedi Vijay Prakash</title><link>https://ntu-nail.github.io/author/dwivedi-vijay-prakash/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jun 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ntu-nail.github.io/author/dwivedi-vijay-prakash/</guid><description>&lt;p>I am a PhD student in Machine Learning at Nanyang Technological University, Singapore being supervised by Prof. Luu Anh Tuan (NTU) and Prof. Xavier Bresson (NUS). My primary interest is in developing deep learning algorithms and architectures on graph-structured data and exploring their applications in computational science applications.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Before starting my PhD, I worked with Prof. Bresson as a Research Assistant in the same lab. I have a background in Computer Science and Engineering (B.Tech.) from MNNIT Allahabad where I explored the fields of Natural Language Processing and Multi-Modal Computing.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Long Range Graph Benchmark</title><link>https://ntu-nail.github.io/publication/long-range-graph-benchmark/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jun 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ntu-nail.github.io/publication/long-range-graph-benchmark/</guid><description>&lt;p>Link: &lt;a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2206.08164" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://arxiv.org/abs/2206.08164&lt;/a>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Recipe for a General, Powerful, Scalable Graph Transformer</title><link>https://ntu-nail.github.io/publication/recipe-for-a-general-powerful-scalable-graph-transformer/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 May 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ntu-nail.github.io/publication/recipe-for-a-general-powerful-scalable-graph-transformer/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2205.12454" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://arxiv.org/abs/2205.12454&lt;/a>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Graph Neural Networks with Learnable Structural and Positional Representations</title><link>https://ntu-nail.github.io/publication/graph-neural-networks-with-learnable-structural-and-positional-representations/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 Oct 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ntu-nail.github.io/publication/graph-neural-networks-with-learnable-structural-and-positional-representations/</guid><description>&lt;p>Link: &lt;a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2110.07875" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://arxiv.org/abs/2110.07875&lt;/a>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Benchmarking Graph Neural Networks</title><link>https://ntu-nail.github.io/publication/benchmarking-graph-neural-networks/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pub